title: Sepp Kuss wins Spanish Vuelta, first American in a decade to win a Grand Tour race
description: A decade later, the United States has a Grand Tour winner again.

title: Letter showing Pope Pius XII had detailed information from German Jesuit about Nazi holocaust
description: ROME — Newly discovered correspondence suggests that World War II-era Pope Pius XII had detailed information from a trusted German Jesuit that up to 6,000 Jews and Poles were being gassed each day in German-occupied Poland.

title: North Korean leader Kim on way home from Russia after Putin meeting
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un departed Russia Sunday, ending a six-day trip that triggered global concerns about weapons transfer deals between the countries.

title: Death toll in Libya flooding hits 11,300 as rescuers search for another 10,000 who are missing
description: The death toll from the unprecedented flooding in Libya rose to 11,300, according to the United Nations, with 10,100 people still missing in Derna city alone.
